se.hig.dvg329.algomaze.control.solvers

Class FibonacciHeap<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • se.hig.dvg329.algomaze.control.solvers.FibonacciHeap<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - The type of objects that this FibonacciHeap can contain.

    public class FibonacciHeap<E>
extends java.lang.Object
    The FibonacciHeap is a priority queue. The FibonacciHeap should be used over other types of heaps when the number of decreaseKey(Node, double) operations outnumber the dequeueMin() operations. All credit for this implementation goes to Keith Schwarz. You can find his implementation here: http://keithschwarz.com/interesting/code/?dir=fibonacci-heap.
    Since:
    1.0.0
    Version:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    Keith Schwarz (htiek@cs.stanford.edu), modified by Thomas Lundgren

      • decreaseKey

        public void decreaseKey(FibonacciHeap.Node<E> node,
                        double newPriority)
                 throws HeapEmptyException,
                        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Decreases the key (priority) of a specified Node. The passed in Node is assumed to exists within the FibonacciHeap for efficiency reasons.
        Parameters:
        node - the Node which priority should be decreased.
        newPriority - the Nodes new priority.
        Throws:
        HeapEmptyException - if an application tries to decrease the priority of an element in an empty FibonacciHeap.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if an application supplies a priority of a Node in the FibonacciHeap that is higher than its current priority.

      • delete

        Parameters:
